<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 6:58PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Paulding and northwestern Cobb Counties through 730 PM EDT...
At 658 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Due West, or 8 miles
west of Marietta, moving southwest at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Marietta, Kennesaw, Acworth, Hiram, Cross Roads, Due West, Lost
Mountain Park and New Hope.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
